Sentencas: A comprehensive 3D theoretical model has been developed to investigate the performance and thermal stress distributions of planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with functionally graded electrodes, at an intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Investigations of solid oxide fuel cells with functionally graded electrodes for high performance and safe thermal stress

Sentencas: The model includes the equations of charge transport, conservation of mass, momentum, and energy along with the thermal stress and strains.
Titulo: Investigations of solid oxide fuel cells with functionally graded electrodes for high performance and safe thermal stress

Sentencas: The comprehensive model is simulated numerically and the numerical results are validated using experimental data.
Titulo: Investigations of solid oxide fuel cells with functionally graded electrodes for high performance and safe thermal stress

Sentencas: The constituent fraction ratio and porosity distribution of each electrode are controlled with a material grading parameter m. Results indicate that the solid oxide fuel cell with functionally graded electrodes perform better than the conventional cell.
Titulo: Investigations of solid oxide fuel cells with functionally graded electrodes for high performance and safe thermal stress

Sentencas: The power density has shown 23% increase at a working voltage of 0.6 V using functionally graded electrodes with the material grading parameter m = 2.0.
Titulo: Investigations of solid oxide fuel cells with functionally graded electrodes for high performance and safe thermal stress

Sentencas: Furthermore, the maximum Von Misses stress corresponding to m = 2.0 is less than half the yield stress at both cathode and electrolyte, while they exceed the yield limit for conventional electrodes (constant porosity at electrodes) at the same working conditions.
Titulo: Investigations of solid oxide fuel cells with functionally graded electrodes for high performance and safe thermal stress

Sentencas: The current results can guide designers of solid oxide fuel cells to adopt functionally graded electrodes for higher performance outcomes and safer thermal stress.
Titulo: Investigations of solid oxide fuel cells with functionally graded electrodes for high performance and safe thermal stress
